As-shot white balance gains (R, G, B) are stored in the CinemaDNG or
ProRes RAW metadata. GIOP applies the inverse of these gains before
the D-Gamut-to-ACES matrix.

5. ISO AND SENSOR CHARACTERISTICS

  DJI cameras use a dual-gain sensor architecture.

  Zenmuse X9 / Ronin 4D (Full-Frame):
    Native ISO (Low Gain) : 400
    Native ISO (High Gain): 1600
    Read noise (High): ~1.2 e-
    Full well capacity (Low): ~45,000 e-
    Dynamic range: 14 stops (SNR=1)

  Zenmuse X7 (Super 35):
    Native ISO (Low Gain) : 500
    Native ISO (High Gain): 2000
    Read noise: ~1.5 e-
    Full well capacity: ~38,000 e-
    Dynamic range: 13.5 stops

  The IDT is gain-state independent. The same inverse D-Log and matrix
  apply. ISO metadata is used for noise profiling only.

6. METADATA HANDLING
  DJI CinemaDNG and ProRes RAW containers carry:
    - Log curve flag (D-Log)
    - ISO / Gain state
    - White balance (Kelvin + tint)
    - Lens data (DL-mount metadata)

  GIOP reads these values. If metadata is absent, the IDT defaults to
  D-Log, ISO 400 Low Gain, and Daylight.

